# Global CLAUDE.md  (copy to ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md)
#
# Loads in EVERY project. Keep it personal and stable, ~100 lines max.
# This makes the shared knowledge base available whatever repo you're in.

## Who I am
Developer + product manager. I work across repos under ~/Documents/NJ_claude.
Be concise and direct; treat me as technical.

## Always-available knowledge base
- @~/Documents/NJ_claude/pm-collab/knowledge-base/product-context.md
- @~/Documents/NJ_claude/pm-collab/knowledge-base/glossary.md
- @~/Documents/NJ_claude/pm-collab/knowledge-base/voice-and-style.md

## Writing
- Lead with the decision/ask; rationale after. Plain language, active voice.
- Use glossary terms exactly. Quantify claims. No filler, no overselling.
- PRDs follow pm-collab/prds/_TEMPLATE.md.

## Code defaults
- <your languages / formatter / test command>
- Run tests before suggesting a commit. Small, focused commits.
- Prefer plan mode for multi-file changes; show impact before editing.

## Workflow
- Never push to main directly; propose a PR.
- Before side-effecting actions (Jira tickets, comments, publishing), show what will
  happen and wait for my confirmation.

## Never
- Never store secrets or PII in any file.
- Never edit Confluence pages directly — they're an auto-published mirror of Git.
